      "content": "<p>The Australian Nepalese Multicultural Centre (ANMC) is a community organisation dedicated to preserving and promoting Nepali culture and heritage in Australia. The ANMC Temple serves as a spiritual home for the Nepali and broader community , conducting daily worship services and celebrating major Nepali Hindu festivals.</p><p><br></p><p>We are currently seeking multiple dedicated and experienced Temple Priests (Pujari) to join our community in Melbourne, Victoria.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>The Temple Priest is responsible for performing daily worship and rituals, maintaining the spiritual and physical order of the temple, and providing religious and cultural guidance to devotees. The successful candidates will work closely with the ANMC Executive Committee to ensure the temple operates in accordance with Hindu traditions and ANMC‚Äôs established policies.</p><p>This is a minimum one-year contract position with the possibility of renewal , commencing in December 2025 or as mutually agreed.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities Include:</strong></p><ul><li>Performing daily morning and evening worship, including puja and aarti, on time and with proper procedure.</li><li>Officiating religious ceremonies and major festivals such as Dashain, Tihar, Teej, Janmashtami, and Shivaratri.</li><li>Maintaining the temple‚Äôs cleanliness and spiritual purity, including caring for idols, altars, and prayer materials.</li><li>Providing blessings, answering religious queries, and guiding devotees respectfully.</li><li>Keeping records of rituals and donations and maintaining the temple calendar.</li><li>Assisting in promoting temple activities and participating in community programs.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Mandatory Requirements</strong></p><p>All applicants <strong>must</strong> hold the following:</p><ul><li>ANMC Life Membership.</li><li>A valid Victorian Working With Children Check (WWCC).</li><li>A current National Police Check.</li><li>An ABN and Public Liability insurance.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Qualifications and Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Demonstrated expertise in Hindu rituals and Vedic traditions, particularly those practiced in Nepal.</li><li>Strong knowledge of Sanskrit and fluency in both Nepali and English (reading, writing, and speaking).</li><li>Familiarity with Nepali cultural and festival practices.</li><li>Prior experience as a temple priest or community religious officiant is preferred.</li><li>Basic computer literacy for records and communication.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Remuneration</strong></p><p>ANMC will pay the priest at an hourly rate on ABN for services at the temple , with additional payment for specific religious rituals conducted. All fees, dakshina, and donations made at the temple are the property of ANMC.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p><p>Applicants must submit the following documents to info@anmcinc.org.au :</p><ol><li>A detailed resume.</li><li>A cover letter explaining your ritual experience, cultural understanding, and motivation to serve at ANMC.</li><li>Copies of your WWCC and Police Check (or intension of application).</li><li>Contact details of referees and any relevant certifications.</li></ol><p><br></p><p><strong>Applications Close: Friday, December 12, 2025.</strong></p><p>Only shortlisted candidates will be invited for an interview and assessment.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Full Position Description</strong></p><p>Please download the full Position Description for complete details on the role, working conditions, and financial protocols.</p><p><a href=\"https://anmcinc.org.au/wp-content/uploads/Position-Description-Priest.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Position Description Priest Download</a></p>",
